<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" class="dark">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="csrf-token" content={get_csrf_token()} />
    <title>Terms of Service -- loopctl</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link phx-track-static rel="stylesheet" href={~p"/assets/app.css"} />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-slate-950 text-slate-300 font-body antialiased">
    <nav class="sticky top-0 z-50 bg-slate-950/90 backdrop-blur-sm border-b border-slate-800">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 h-14 flex items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/" class="font-mono text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">loopctl</a>
        <a
          href="/"
          class="text-sm text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-200 transition-colors"
        >
          Back to home
        </a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-slate-100">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-500">Last updated: April 1, 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p>
            By accessing or using loopctl ("the Service"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.
            If you do not agree, do not use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p>
            loopctl is an agent-native project state store that provides API primitives for
            chain-of-custody verification, review enforcement, and progress tracking in AI
            development workflows. The Service is provided as a multi-tenant SaaS platform.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">
            3. API Keys and Authentication
          </h2>
          <p>
            You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your API keys.
            You agree not to share API keys with unauthorized parties. All activity under
            your API key is your responsibility.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">4. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You agree not to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
            <li>Use the Service to violate any applicable law or regulation</li>
            <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the Service or its infrastructure</li>
            <li>
              Interfere with or disrupt the Service or the servers or networks connected to it
            </li>
            <li>Use the Service to store or transmit malicious code</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">5. Data and Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Your data is isolated via PostgreSQL Row-Level Security. We do not access your
            tenant data except as necessary to provide the Service or as required by law.
            See our
            <a href="/privacy" class="text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-300">Privacy Policy</a>
            for details.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">6. Service Availability</h2>
          <p>
            We strive to maintain high availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted access.
            The Service is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, loopctl and its operators shall not be
            liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages
            resulting from your use of or inability to use the Service.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">8. Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Continued use of the
            Service after changes constitutes acceptance of the modified terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-200 mb-3">9. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about these terms, open an issue on the <a
              href="https://github.com/mkreyman/loopctl"
              class="text-accent-400 hover:text-accent-300"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >GitHub repository</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>

    <footer class="border-t border-slate-800 bg-slate-950">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-8">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between text-xs text-slate-400">
          <p>&copy; {DateTime.utc_now().year} loopctl. All rights reserved.</p>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-6">
            <a href="/terms" class="text-slate-300">Terms</a>
            <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-slate-300 transition-colors">Privacy</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
